Introduction

Super Junior-M (short for Super Junior - Mandarin) is a sub-unit of the boy group SUPER JUNIOR under SM Entertainment.

The group made their debut with the first album 'Me' with a 7-member lineup consisting of Hangeng, Siwon, Zhoumi, Donghae, Henry, Ryeowook, and Kyuhyun. In late 2009, Hangeng chose to leave Super Junior altogether, thus leaving the unit as well.

In 2011, with the addition of members Sungmin and Eunhyuk, the unit made a comeback with their 2nd mini album 'Perfection'.

The group has been on an indefinite hiatus since 2015, with member Henry leaving in 2020.
